.TH "mangle_path" 9 "mangle_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mangle_path \- mangle and copy path to buffer beginning
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" mangle_path
.BI "(char *s "  ","
.BI "const char *p "  ","
.BI "const char *esc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "s" 12
buffer start
.IP "p" 12
beginning of path in above buffer
.IP "esc" 12
set of characters that need escaping

Copy the path from \fIp\fP to \fIs\fP, replacing each occurrence of character from
\fIesc\fP with usual octal escape.
Returns pointer past last written character in \fIs\fP, or NULL in case of
failure.
